---
import SiteLayout from '../../../components/SiteLayout.astro';

const title = 'Wired or wireless gaming keyboard? Which is better?';
const description =
  'Wired vs wireless gaming keyboards: real differences in latency, battery, comfort and price. A direct guide to choosing based on how you play.';

const fecha = 'June 12, 2026';
const dateISO = '2026-06-12';
const tiempoLectura = '4 min read';

const secciones = [
  { id: 'latencia', label: 'Latency: can you tell?' },
  { id: 'bateria', label: 'Battery and endurance' },
  { id: 'conectividad', label: 'Wireless connectivity types' },
  { id: 'cable-ventajas', label: 'Advantages of the cable' },
  { id: 'precio', label: 'Price difference' },
  { id: 'conclusion', label: 'Which to choose?' },
];
---

<SiteLayout title={`${title} | Monckey Gamer`} description={description} robots="index, follow" article={{ title, dateISO }}>
  <article class="post">
    <a class="category-back" href="/en/blog/">← Back to Blog</a>

    <header class="post-header">
      <span class="post-tag"><span class="post-tag-gg">GG</span> Gamer guide · Peripherals</span>
      <h1>Wired or wireless gaming keyboard?</h1>
      <p class="post-lead">
        Three years ago the answer was clear: cable for serious gaming. Today the situation has changed
        radically and wireless technology is no longer a disadvantage.
      </p>
      <div class="post-meta">
        <span>{fecha}</span>
        <span class="post-meta-dot"></span>
        <span>{tiempoLectura}</span>
      </div>
    </header>

    <nav class="post-toc" aria-label="Article contents">
      <span class="post-toc-title">In this article</span>
      <ul>
        {secciones.map((s) => (
          <li><a href={`#${s.id}`}>{s.label}</a></li>
        ))}
      </ul>
    </nav>

    <div class="post-body">
      <section id="latencia">
        <h2>Latency: can you tell the difference in gaming?</h2>
        <p>
          The latency of a modern wireless keyboard via a <strong>2.4GHz USB receiver</strong>
          is roughly 1ms, the same as many wired keyboards. In gaming, even in
          top-level competitive shooters, that difference is undetectable to a human.
        </p>
        <p>
          The latency you can notice is Bluetooth's: 8–40ms depending on profile and device.
          <strong>Bluetooth is not recommended for competitive gaming</strong>, but it is fine for
          casual use or when you want to connect to a TV or tablet.
        </p>
        <p class="post-note">
          Bottom line: for gaming, 2.4GHz = cable in practice. Bluetooth only for casual use.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section id="bateria">
        <h2>Battery: how long do wireless keyboards last?</h2>
        <p>
          Modern wireless keyboards with RGB on last between <strong>15 and 40 hours</strong>.
          With RGB off, some models reach 200–500 hours.
        </p>
        <ul class="post-list">
          <li>
            The <a href="/en/keyboards/redthunder-k75-wireless-75pct-hotswap-2/">RedThunder K75 Wireless</a>
            offers USB-C charging and enough battery for weeks of normal use.
          </li>
          <li>
            The <a href="/en/keyboards/aula-s75-pro-screen-knob-trimode-7/">AULA S75 Pro Tri-mode</a>
            has a long-lasting battery with an automatic power-saving mode.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Most charge over USB-C while you keep using them. No need to stop.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section id="conectividad">
        <h2>Wireless connectivity types</h2>
        <div class="post-table-wrap">
          <table class="post-table">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Technology</th>
                <th>Latency</th>
                <th>For gaming</th>
                <th>Range</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td>USB Cable</td><td>~1 ms</td><td>Perfect</td><td>Cable length</td></tr>
              <tr><td>2.4GHz USB</td><td>~1 ms</td><td>Perfect</td><td>~10 m</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Bluetooth 5.0</td><td>8–20 ms</td><td>Casual / TV</td><td>~10 m</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Bluetooth 5.3+</td><td>5–10 ms</td><td>Casual</td><td>~10 m</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
        <p>
          The best wireless gaming keyboards offer <strong>triple connectivity</strong>:
          USB-C cable + 2.4GHz receiver + Bluetooth. That way you choose based on the context.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section id="cable-ventajas">
        <h2>When choosing the cable makes sense</h2>
        <ul class="post-list">
          <li>Professional competition or tournaments demanding zero risk of interference.</li>
          <li>Tight budget: wired keyboards are cheaper for the same features.</li>
          <li>You never want to worry about charging a battery.</li>
          <li>
            You want maximum connection stability in environments full of Wi-Fi signals
            and Bluetooth devices that could create interference.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          The <a href="/en/keyboards/redragon-mechanical-wired-hotswap-red-4/">Redragon Mechanical Hot-swap</a>
          is an example of an excellent wired mechanical keyboard for gaming with zero battery worries.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section id="precio">
        <h2>Price difference: how much more does wireless cost?</h2>
        <p>
          At the same tier and build quality, a wireless keyboard costs 20% to 40%
          more than its wired equivalent. The difference comes from the battery, the radio module and
          the included USB receiver.
        </p>
        <p>
          On budget options like the
          <a href="/en/keyboards/aula-f75-pro-wireless-75pct-reaper-3/">AULA F75 Pro Wireless</a>
          or the <a href="/en/keyboards/aula-f75-pro-white-wireless-knob-5/">AULA F75 Pro White Wireless</a>,
          the premium over the cable is minimal and worth it for the convenience.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section id="conclusion">
        <h2>Which to choose for your case?</h2>
        <ul class="post-list">
          <li>
            <strong>Serious competitive gaming:</strong> 2.4GHz wireless or cable. Both are equally
            valid in 2026.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Casual gaming + clean desk:</strong> wireless without a second thought.
            The cable is an unnecessary nuisance.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Tight budget:</strong> a quality wired mechanical, always.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Mixed use (PC + TV + tablet):</strong> tri-mode with Bluetooth to connect to everything.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Compare all our keyboards in the <a href="/en/keyboards/">gaming keyboards</a> catalog,
          filtering by connectivity and format.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>

    <aside class="post-cta">
      <h3>Wired or wireless, we have it</h3>
      <p>Mechanical gaming keyboards with the connectivity options you are looking for.</p>
      <a class="btn" href="/en/keyboards/">View gaming keyboards</a>
    </aside>
  </article>
</SiteLayout>

<style>
  .post { max-width: 760px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .post-header { margin: 18px 0 32px; }
  .post-tag { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 7px; font-size: 0.68rem; font-weight: 500; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.14em; color: #8aa0b8; }
  .post-tag-gg { font-weight: 800; letter-spacing: 0.05em; color: #7cffcb; border: 1px solid rgba(124,255,203,0.3); border-radius: 5px; padding: 1px 5px; font-size: 0.62rem; }
  .post-header h1 { margin: 18px 0 16px; font-size: clamp(1.6rem,6vw,2.8rem); line-height: 1.15; overflow-wrap: break-word; }
  .post-lead { margin: 0 0 18px; color: #c8d8e8; font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.7; }
  .post-meta { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 12px; color: #8aa0b8; font-size: 0.9rem; }
  .post-meta-dot { width: 4px; height: 4px; border-radius: 50%; background: #8aa0b8; }
  .post-toc { margin: 0 0 40px; padding: 24px 28px; border-radius: 20px; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.02); border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08); }
  .post-toc-title { display: block; font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: #7cffcb; margin-bottom: 14px; }
  .post-toc ul { margin: 0; padding: 0; list-style: none; display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2,minmax(0,1fr)); gap: 10px 24px; }
  .post-toc a { color: #c8d8e8; text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.95rem; transition: color 0.2s ease; }
  .post-toc a:hover { color: #7cffcb; }
  .post-body section { margin-bottom: 40px; scroll-margin-top: 24px; }
  .post-body h2 { font-size: 1.5rem; color: #e6f7ff; margin: 0 0 16px; padding-left: 14px; border-left: 3px solid #7cffcb; }
  .post-body p { color: #c8d8e8; line-height: 1.8; margin: 0 0 16px; }
  .post-body strong { color: #e6f7ff; }
  .post-body a { color: #7cffcb; text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 3px; }
  .post-list { margin: 0 0 16px; padding: 0; list-style: none; display: grid; gap: 12px; }
  .post-list li { color: #c8d8e8; line-height: 1.7; padding-left: 26px; position: relative; }
  .post-list li::before { content: ""; position: absolute; left: 4px; top: 11px; width: 7px; height: 7px; border-radius: 50%; background: #7cffcb; }
  .post-table-wrap { margin: 0 0 18px; overflow-x: auto; border-radius: 16px; border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08); }
  .post-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.95rem; }
  .post-table th { text-align: left; padding: 14px 20px; color: #7cffcb; font-size: 0.78rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03); border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08); }
  .post-table td { padding: 13px 20px; color: #c8d8e8; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.05); }
  .post-table tbody tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
  .post-table td:first-child { color: #e6f7ff; font-weight: 500; }
  .post-note { background: rgba(27,183,255,0.06); border: 1px solid rgba(27,183,255,0.18); border-radius: 14px; padding: 16px 20px; color: #c8d8e8 !important; font-size: 0.95rem; }
  .post-cta { margin-top: 48px; padding: 36px; border-radius: 24px; text-align: center; background: linear-gradient(135deg,rgba(0,255,225,0.06),rgba(27,183,255,0.06)); border: 1px solid rgba(124,255,203,0.15); }
  .post-cta h3 { margin: 0 0 8px; font-size: 1.4rem; color: #e6f7ff; }
  .post-cta p { margin: 0 0 20px; color: #c8d8e8; }
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .post-toc { padding: 20px; margin-bottom: 28px; }
    .post-toc ul { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .post-lead { font-size: 1rem; }
    .post-meta { flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; }
    .post-body section { margin-bottom: 32px; }
    .post-body h2 { font-size: 1.3rem; }
    .post-table { font-size: 0.85rem; }
    .post-table th { padding: 11px 12px; font-size: 0.7rem; }
    .post-table td { padding: 10px 12px; }
    .post-cta { padding: 28px 20px; }
    .post-cta h3 { font-size: 1.25rem; }
    .post-cta .btn { width: 100%; }
  }
  @media (max-width: 380px) {
    .post-table th, .post-table td { padding: 9px 10px; font-size: 0.8rem; }
  }
</style>
